04/06/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Kosovo government has initiated a campaign to promote the fulfilment of international standards for the province, Albanian Daily News reported on Friday (4 June), quoting Kosovo Albanian television KohaVision. 
Government spokesperson Mimoza Kusari said meeting the standards is crucial to further development.
In other news, the finance and economy ministry announced Thursday that the government has decided to increase to 16m euros the amount it intends to spend on rebuilding Serb homes destroyed during clashes in March. 
UNMIK has said that rebuilding the homes tops its list of current priorities. 
(Albanian Daily News, Glas Javnosti, B92, AFP - 03/06/04)
